nal battalion deploys to Iraq Associated Press - May 30, 2007 9:34 PM ET WHEATON, Ill. (AP) - The daughter of US Supreme Court Justice Antonin Scalia faces 18 months of court supervision after pleading guilty today to drunken driving. Ann Banaszewski (ban-uh-CHEF'-skee) was arrested in February and charged with driving under the influence and child endangerment. Police say three children were in Banaszewski's minivan when she was stopped and refused to take a breath test for alcohol. A license suspension is automatic in such cases. A spokesman for the DuPage County State's Attorney's office says Banaszewski, who lives in Wheaton, must also pay a fine of $$2,155 and work 140 hours of public service. Scalia began serving on the Supreme Court in 1986. He has nine children. Copyright 2007 The Associated Press. All rights reserved. This material may not be published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed. News from the heartland of Illinois and Iowa. Business headlines, stock prices, and financial tips. Headlines from in, around and dealing with the classroom. City By City Online News, links, and information for your community. WQAD.com covers 32 counties in eastern Iowa and western Illinois. Healthy Quad Cities May Early diagnosis and appropriate management of arthritis, including self-management activities, can help people with arthritis decrease pain, improve function, stay productive, and lower health care costs. Take a test drive of the Dutchman Express-Extended, the Kodiak Expandable or Pilgrim Fifth Wheel from Kamper Korner. Eat Local for Less We&#39;ve worked out deals with some of our area&#39;s best restaurants to give you 1/2 off gift certificates - $50 gift certificates for only $25! But you have to be fast - there are only a limited number of gift certificates. Download the Weather Wizard Powerful weather tools, current conditions, news headlines, and more! Includes quick-tips on how to use all the features. All content &copy; Copyright 2001 - 2007 WorldNow 